The paper deals with image recognition, specifically multi-label image recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves graph representation learning, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of statistical label co-occurrence, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
